      explanation: `## Marine Animal Stings

Many sea creatures can sting you, including jellyfish, stingrays, and sea urchins.

## Common Marine Stings
- **Jellyfish**: Tentacles sting when touched
- **Stingrays**: Barb in tail can puncture skin
- **Sea urchins**: Sharp spines can break off in skin

## What to Do for Jellyfish Sting
- Get out of the water
- Rinse with vinegar (or seawater if no vinegar)
- Remove tentacles carefully (protect your hands)
- Do NOT use fresh water (makes it worse)

## When to Get Help
- Trouble breathing
- Chest pain
- Severe swelling
- Sting covers large area`,
