      explanation: `## Types of Marine Envenomation

### Cnidarians (Jellyfish, Man-of-War)
- Nematocysts inject venom
- Pain, redness, welts
- Rarely: severe systemic reaction
- Treatment: vinegar, remove tentacles, pain relief

### Stingrays
- Puncture wound with venom injection
- Severe pain
- Treatment: hot water immersion (113F/45C)
- May need wound exploration

### Sea Urchins
- Spine punctures with venom
- Pain and inflammation
- Treatment: remove accessible spines, hot water

### Venomous Fish (Scorpionfish, Lionfish)
- Spine envenomation
- Severe pain
- Treatment: hot water immersion

## General Treatment Principles
- Control pain
- Wound care
- Tetanus update
- Watch for infection`,
