      explanation: `## Advanced Toxinology

### Cnidarian Venom Components
- CfTX: Chironex pore-forming toxin
- PhTX: Portuguese man-of-war toxin
- Mechanism: calcium-permeable pores
- Dose-dependent cardiac toxicity

### Irukandji Molecular Mechanism
- Catecholamine excess syndrome
- Possible direct myocardial toxicity
- Troponin elevation common
- Takotsubo-like picture

### Fish Venom Proteins
- Stonustoxin (stonefish): 150kDa
- Hyaluronidase: venom spread
- Heat denaturation at 50C

## Evidence Base

### Hot Water Therapy
- Effective for fish, echinoderm envenomation
- 45C optimal temperature
- Duration 30-90 minutes
- Pain relief within minutes

### Vinegar Controversy
- Effective for box jellyfish
- May worsen some species (Australian data)
- Seawater rinse alternative
- Do not use freshwater (osmotic nematocyst discharge)

### Box Jellyfish Antivenom
- CSL antivenom (Australia)
- Neutralizes Chironex venom
- Efficacy debated for cardiac effects
- May reduce local necrosis

## Special Considerations

### Marine Wound Infections
- Vibrio vulnificus: severe, rapidly progressive
- Aeromonas species
- Mycobacterium marinum (delayed)
- Antibiotics: fluoroquinolone + doxycycline

### Geographic Variation
- Box jellyfish: Australia, SE Asia
- Portuguese man-of-war: Atlantic, Pacific
- Stonefish: Indo-Pacific
- Local protocols may vary`,
